        "username": "the_new_mr",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/the_new_mr/{size}/9396_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-08-31T04:07:28.826Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Currently, the cancel button when editing a message is over on the left. This greatly reduces the amount of room available for the message input text field. I prefer the Signal behaviour over WhatsApp which uses the back button to cancel since it’s possible in Signal to use the back button to leave a chat mid-edit and then return to the chat to continue the message edit. However, if the cancel edit button was moved over to the right above or below the complete edit button, it would greatly enhance the user experience.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 3,
        "updated_at": "2025-08-31T05:37:47.357Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
